title.label: Fun and Unique, but too Limited

content.label:
Cut the Rope: Magic is an overall good game. There are many unique mechanics such as turning Om-Nom small, the antagonist (Wizard Spider), and the modernized graphics compared to older Cut the Rope games. 

I would have rated it a 4 out of 5 or even a 5 out of 5 stars, but the reason why it is held back at a 3 out of 5 is because of how limited the gameplay is. Om-Nom tends to get full too quickly and it takes a while for him to completely regain his appetite. 

Om-Nom‚Äôs appetite system doesn‚Äôt mean that the game is absolutely terrible though; I still enjoy playing it whenever Om-Nom is hungry due to the previously mentioned factors it has. It is diverse, it is formatted similarly to Cut the Rope 2, and I also enjoy upsetting the Wizard Spider when I succeed to give the candy to Om-Nom.

This game is overall fun and unique and I feel like the rating I gave it is well-deserved.
